    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-02-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-02-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="1605"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1605">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.51/105.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">French Ambassador</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1449.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 4, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                    receipt of your excellency’s note of January 25, 1915, in which you ask the
                    Department to inform you [etc.]</p>
                <p>In reply I have the honor to inform your excellency that the Department appears
                    to have no information regarding the reported seizure of the rifles and
                    ammunition mentioned. However, a telegram has been sent to the American Consul
                    at Vera Cruz to report <pb facs="1175" n="1059" xml:id="pg_1059"/> on the
                    matter, and when his report is received you will be promptly informed.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
